<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Provisional financing figures for Feb 1997.</title>
<headline>Provisional financing figures for Feb 1997.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-03-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Financing of 1199.8 million rand was obtained in government bonds while net short-term loans increased by 1242.2 million rand during February this year, the South African Finance Department said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>This brought the total financing for that month to 2442 million rand, the department said in a statement.</p>
<p>				   February 1997	April 1996 -</p>
<p>							    February 1997</p>
<p>				   (R'million)</p>
<p>Government bonds and</p>
<p>    debentures		 1199.8		 33843.2</p>
<p>Short-term (net)</p>
<p>	 Bridging Bonds	   0.0		 -3616.5</p>
<p>	 Tender Bills	   400.0		  3600.0</p>
<p>	 Corporation for</p>
<p>	  Public Deposits(2)  842.2		  2437.2</p>
<p>    Foreign Loans		 0.0		  2831.0</p>
<p>				   ______		 _______</p>
<p>    Total financing	  2442.0		 39094.9</p>
<p>Government bonds and debentures to the amount of 16138 million rand and foreign loans to the amount of 1554 million rand were redeemed during April 1996 to February 1997, the statement said.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom, 27-11 482-1003</p>
